title: Ulbrichts
extract: The historic region of Austria is the birthplace of the esteemed surname Ulbricht. The name is derived from "Ulbricht," a personal name of Teutonic origin, popular in various forms throughout Europe during the Middle Ages, meaning "illustrious."
